Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Cook meat, onion, celery and carrot in large saucepan about 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in undrained tomatoes, broth, basil, thyme and 3/4 cup water. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes. Serve over spaghetti. Garnish with carrot and basil, if desired.